			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Unified Format for Language Documents</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/VadimZaytsev.html">Vadim Zaytsev</a>, <a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_13">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_13</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2e.html"><span class="tagM">T2E: Documentation</span></a><ul><li> The focus is on representing and organizing language documentation in a unified, reusable format.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It is oriented toward tool-supported processing/management of language documents (e.g., extracting/transforming artifacts).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> The work treats language descriptions as analyzable/manipulable artifacts, enabling consistency and reuse checks.
</li></ul></li></ul>
